{
  "stem": "7598.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] We had the, the bombs falling down, and we used to hide in ditches.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Very much like the Pied Piper, you, you get into a state where you, you just do what, mostly what other people do.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Except that we were in one ditch and for some peculiar reason my uncle said, let's get across the road.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we all ran across.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And as we ran across, a bomb fell in the other ditch, and people got killed, which is a little incident my grandchildren always find quite amazing.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I suppose so do I.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We walked and walked, and eventually we found a big farm.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I think there must have been about 100 refugees that took refuge there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "In the middle of the night, we heard soldiers marching.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So there was that sound, and then we listened, and we realized it was the goose step.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "At that point, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the religious Jews, the ones who wore the payots and the beards, all tore up their passports.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My uncle didn't, because he was born in Belgium, and he wanted to hang on to his.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But I, I very much remember people tearing their passports and burning them in the straw.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But although he had a very Jewish name, Rubinstein.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "At about, I suppose, 1 o'clock in the morning or so, a young German soldier came in, flashed his torch and said, are you all Aryan, in German.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we said, yes, and he walked out, which is amazing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] When I think about it objectively, I can understand it all.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They weren't trained.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were victorious.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They didn't know what to do.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
